How to maintain the silver-plated jewelry Gold plated or silver plated jewelry is made by covering a base metal with a very thin layer of gold/silver, compared to other types of metal, this is more reactive. So it is necessary to protect the gold/silver plated by following our tips below:

• Be sure to keep silver plated/gold plated items away from water, soaps, makeup and perfumes. Take off your jewelry before washing or bathing. 

• Keep it away from hard surfaces, even a light scratch will cause the layer to wear away fast

• Clean it gently with soft cloth or an appropriate jewelry cleaner, this could help to eliminate any dirt or dust which will wear away the layer on the jewelry surface.

• When not wearing your jewelry, store it in a dry area
